cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the formation of a network among relay stations in next generation wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses game theory to model the behavior of the relay stations, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the utility function and the bit error rate, which are related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also proposes a distributed algorithm, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
